y may implement loot n scoot in their own actions if they so choose but the Progeny member cannot tell someone they must loot n scoot unless the Progeny member ALWAYS abide by it as well.<br><br>The guild as a whole is not required to loot n scoot but are permitted if you so choose to make an attempt at avenging your death ONCE at any time you see fit whether alone or bringing reinforcements. This gives the opportunity to square up any unfair deaths. If you cannot defeat them with this chance than most likely you will not be victorious with the next.<br><br>Upon being killed outside of scheduled raids and wars, those in Progeny who choose not to abide by loot n scoot do not have to leave the zone. Understand that staying in the zone you risk being killed repeatedly as you try to return to your hunt. Keep in mind however that if it becomes excessive torment from the same aggressor they can be petitioned for harrassment.<br><br>I reccomend to all of you that if you fall you should drag your corpse away to loot it. This helps thwart corpse camping.<br><br>&lt;recent edit to the policy&gt;<br>If someone falls to you, move on from their corpse unless they have fallen at a vantage point where you feel you should stay. Should you be present when they return to loot, they are not to be spoken to or attacked unless they initiate another attack or remain at the vantage point in which they have fallen. <br>&lt;end of edit&gt;<br><br>Should you run into difficulties in which you are unsure what course of action to take, consult the officers.<br><br>At no point is any other guild or guild member to be slandered for either abiding or not abiding by loot n scoot. It is not our right to dictate how other guilds should be run.<br><br>End guidelines<br><br>Now, this is not submitted for your approval. It is only to make you aware of what we have taken from the debate in a form to improve our guild workings.<br><br>You will all have your own opinions to which we all have the right. Is there really a need to condemn us for it?<br><br>~Kayramidnight~<br>Guild Mistress<br>Progeny of Hate <p></p><i>Edited by <A HREF=http://pub7.ezboard.com/btallonzektimes4735.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kayramidnight>Kayramidnight</A> at: 7/13/00 8:58:48 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000028><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub7.ezboard.com/uvyshnu.showPublicProfile>Vyshnu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br>   <font color=#FFFF00>(5/18/00 7:48:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub77.ezboard.com/ftallonzektimes4735guildsoftallonzek.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=33.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/generaleq/vyshnu.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Progeny of Hate PvP Guidelines</span><hr size=1> oo oo, can i join??  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#00000F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub7.ezboard.com/uvaedaen.showPublicProfile>vaedaen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br>   <font color=#FFFF00>(5/19/00 10:58:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub77.ezboard.com/ftallonzektimes4735guildsoftallonzek.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=33.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Progeny of Hate PvP Guidelines</span><hr size=1> die vysh! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000028><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub7.ezboard.com/uvyshnu.showPublicProfile>Vyshnu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br>   <font color=#FFFF00>(5/21/00 3:29:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub77.ezboard.com/ftallonzektimes4735guildsoftallonzek.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=33.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/generaleq/vyshnu.jpg HEIGHT=200 WIDTH